phrases: So I am not going to see him anymore.
I told you to stop calling me that.
I just received word that you all passed the exams.
The six of you managed to pull it off.
It seems I have no choice but to approve of Uesugi-kun.
So from tomorrow on, he can come here to...
I am not going to see him anymore.
Also, we have decided to stay at our new place for a while longer.
We are not going to make Ichika do all the work, of course.
I am going to get a job, too.
I am not going to pretend we have become independent or anything.
I know we are not doing the right thing, either.
But I have a feeling that living like that will change us.
I feel like we have made some progress.
Abstract ideas like progress could not be less convincing.
I have seen your so-called new home.
To me, it looks like you have gone backwards.
You must not have forgotten in just five years.
You do not want to live like that anymore, do you?
We need to get back before work.
The path you are about to walk is a thorny one.
You will certainly going to regret it.
I will be taking your daughter, sir.
It seems, happily, that my daughters have all passed the exams.
Am I smiling like I should?
I am their father, after all.
I thought I told you I was done with you.
It seems that relationships require mutual input, unfortunately.
And where did you get this bike?
I borrowed it from my boss.
I told you, I used to do deliveries.
That is when I got my license.
You look shockingly tacky with it.
Are not these your exam results?
I bet it turns out that you got 100 in all subjects.
Uesugi Futaro Japanese Math Science Socials English Total hhhhh89 97 94 91 88 459
I am going to floor it.
My long job as a tutor has come to a close today.
This is the end of our relationship, too.
I thought you were going to floor it.
I am carrying a lot of weight.
You have always been like this.
A jerk of the highest order.
And why is not he reacting at all?
Congratulations on making it through the finals.
I cannot believe we pulled it off.
I want to frame our exam papers.
Why do not we do that when get slightly better grades?
I know we are celebrating, but can we really afford all this?
The owner is treating us to celebrate.
Remember to give us five stars.
Our orders are all over the place, are not they?
I guess this is business as usual for us.
Your predictions on the contemporary literature questions were spot on.
You all helped me out, too, though.
I have to return the favor.
Why do not we all share a little, then?
That is how we made it through the exams, after all.
Plus, this way, we can enjoy all the different flavors.
That is your real motivation, is not it?
I never would have thought you would do the best, Ichika.
I am beating you next time.
I am going to take a short break.
You can handle it from here.
Oh, boss, is it all right if I set aside some pudding?
Sure, but did you ever like pudding?
No, it is in return for a Valentine's Day gift.
I thought you were one of us!
Uh, it was from my sister.
Oh, that is what it was.
I thought it was from one of the five girls.
Actually, I have been getting some all the time since January.
He just went into the back.
I was going to thank him.
I guess I will wait for a bit.
I hope I hid it well.
It is true that I was rooting for Miku... I think.
Nakano Ichika Japanese Math Science Socials English Total hhhhh38 63 52 40 47 240
Miku said she would confess if she came in first.
But I had the highest grade this time.
Thanks for helping with the dishes.
It is in return for the treat.
I will let the boss know.
Forget what I said on the bike.
I am sure I troubled you with what I said.
I think I went too fast.
I have no idea what you are talking about.
I guess he never heard me.
We are not girlfriend material to him anyway.
He never even noticed when Miku gave him Valentine's Day chocolates.
I am actually glad he did not hear me.
Boss, I am done cleaning up.
I am not asking for a response.
If you do not see me as girlfriend material, I will force you to see me that way.
Remember how I said there is got to be
at least one girl on this planet who would fall for a guy like you?
Were not there some shops closer to your place?
It is not like I took a detour to come to this shop in order to have a chance
to run into you based on what I remembered.
I was just walking when I naturally found myself at this shop.
The longest tale in Miku history.
Submit a receipt for over 3,000 yen in purchases
Chance to win a big prize!
Hot spring vouchers for two 5 winners
This is the only place that does it.
This hot spring is near where our Grandpa lives.
You cannot even trade hot spring vouchers for money.
The best prize is obviously Prize E, the gift coupons.
How much would Prize B fetch if you sold it?
I have a feeling you would never win it, Futaro.
We will not know until we try!
There is something Nino wanted me to buy her.
Is there anyone you have a crush on or anything?
There is not anyone in class that you have since developed feelings for?
What is gotten into you, Futaro?
An acquaintance of mine apparently got confessed to by a classmate.
They said they do not need a response, but, uh...
I did not think you would be one to think about that kind of thing.
You are like a normal guy.
I am just asking for someone I know.
I thought you would be the type to dismiss that kind of thing.
What happened to my acquaintance was...
She tried to confess, but she did not have the guts to, apparently.
Once you do, you cannot go back to how things were before.
So it takes a lot of courage.
I guess some people have that courage.
I do not know how to face her anymore.
Why am I such a coward?
Place a check in your desired reward.
Either way, it is spring break.
There is plenty of time to think.
This is all thanks to Onii-chan.
I cannot believe I actually won.
The foremost tourist attraction in the area: the Bell of Vows.
It says, Any man and woman who ring this bell together are forever bound.
Shoot, I forgot to charge it.
I will forget about those girls and enjoy this family vacation.
You guys are all here on a family vacation, too?
You always have to expect something to go wrong when you are traveling.
When did those girls work things out with their dad?
If you have something to say, say it.
The way you said his name, Futaro...
It is been half a year since we met each other.
It is about time we get a bit closer, is not it?
I do agree with that, but...
Never mind that, let us get ready for lunch.
I do not know if I can do it right.
Ichika, could you explain something to me?
Sorry, I am in the middle of something.
We have only been apart for a short while, and they are all being distant.
Go retrieve our lunch boxes from Ebata.
All of us are together for once.
I am spending quality time with my family, privately.
We are probably at the same hotel.
I need to speak with you later.
It is like a haunted house.
When did she get up there?
Good thing there is a mixed bath.
The whole family can be together.
You should not stay in for too long, Onii-chan.
She said she wanted to talk...
Why is she being so roundabout?
Th-The courtyard is this way, right?
I was going to the courtyard.
What did you want to talk about?
L-Let us just go to the courtyard...
I am not letting you get away.
What is your understanding of your relationship with us?
You said we are p-partners or something.
No, we are not partners anymore.
We are not doing lessons very often anymore, so I cannot deny that.
But I have been hired to tutor until you guys graduate.
Until then, as your tutor, I will...
Let us put an end to this relationship.
Tell me what is going on!
Did your father tell you to do this?
Why would you say that now?
Do not you dare lay a hand on my granddaughter.
I am going to sleep forever and fly off into the future.
Onii-chan's flying off into the future.
That is what I would like to ask you!
Why did not you come to the courtyard?
Let us meet up to talk.
I would love to, but we are being watched carefully to make sure we do not see you.
I do not think I can get out.
There is a good place, then.
Okay, seems like you are the real Itsuki this time.
Yesterday, I met you at the front desk, and I was told to stop tutoring.
So that was not you, then, was it?
It could only have been one of my sisters.
One of them is rejecting me.
Did any of them seem suspicious?
Why did they disguise themselves as you?
We seem to bump into each other in the bath a lot.
Want me to wash you or something?
Let me ask you one thing...
I worked up all my courage for nothing.
You were absolutely in the wrong there.
I do not think we are the same in every way.
We are able to tell ourselves apart, after all.
I am sure you could, too.
Here we go again with your crazy theories.
Nino used to hate you so much.
They have all been a bit weird since spring break started.
I called you out last night to ask about that.
Can you think of a reason?
I guess I was not just imagining things when I noticed they have been acting odd.
Our top priority is solving the Fake Itsuki question.
Unless we can figure out what she is really thinking,
I may really be fired as your tutor.
Though, there is something Fake Itsuki said that I agree with.
I do not know what she is after.
But we are not partners working toward the same goal anymore.
Our many days spent studying for exams together,
going to the fireworks festival, school camp, last year's end, and New Year's...
We have shared so much time together now.
Would not you say we are friends at this point?
I will hear you guys out.
